<paragraph id="58E5514204F8DCA4F09746592437E312" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE595A455E45561C89D9AB5F67D8720C" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The holotype is the specimen seen and illustrated by Voets, whose illustration was later copied by 
<bibRefCitation id="4E7829AF020BF98DEE7C5F4A5ECD4049" author="Jablonsky, CG" journalOrPublisher="Joachim Pauli Buchhandler, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/57671828" refId="B21" refString="Jablonsky, CG, 1785. Natursystem aller bekannten in-und auslandischen Insekten, als eine Forsetzung der von Buffonschen Naturgeschichte. Nach der System des Ritters Carl von Linne bearbeitet. Der Kafer erster Theil. Mit sechs illuminirten Kupfertafeln. Joachim Pauli Buchhandler, Berlin, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/57671828" title="Natursystem aller bekannten in-und auslandischen Insekten, als eine Forsetzung der von Buffonschen Naturgeschichte. Nach der System des Ritters Carl von Linne bearbeitet. Der Kafer erster Theil. Mit sechs illuminirten Kupfertafeln." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/57671828" year="1785">Jablonsky (1785</bibRefCitation>
: Plate 4 fig. 4) and is probably lost.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA264C885281899E1BAA897C068042D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C2C7A6080D68B714E20E4E56C6BF4EDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5B9133FEEBD1E59F58328E6005E3D21" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="D16BCC841D708979F7A77E3B5B9B3E0C" baseAuthorityName="Jablonsky in Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1785" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Megasoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megasoma gyas" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyas">
<emphasis id="29D1CA41DE5507C05D60CA63AA6A4EAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Megasoma gyas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Caatinga biome of the Brazilian states of 
<normalizedToken id="9ECEDD65124BCF424671A12062F1D946" originalValue="Piauí">Piaui</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="6BF3636A42AFA12EB2A49BD08BF81625" originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
, Rio Grande do Norte, 
<normalizedToken id="48765F75F7FA10F919B4C4196C98A8D8" originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
, Pernambuco, Alagoas, and Sergipe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C2D55B53354E9B8BCA7F72B871D1B94" captionStart="Figures 9, 10" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 9, 10. 9 Surface of bioma Caatinga in Brazil 10 The subregions in NE Brazil." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.999.53130.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481434" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">9</figureCitation>
). The distribution range of this species overlaps a portion of the &quot;subregioes nordestinas&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="A2D84C1EB52597609B11D63D235A90B2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262010000300019" author="Vasconcellos, A" journalOrPublisher="Cepe, Recife" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B42" refString="Vasconcellos, A, Andreazze, R, Almeida, AM, Araujo, HFP, Oliveira, ES, Oliveira, U, 2010. Seasonality of Insects in the semi-arid Caatinga of Northwestern Brazil - Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 54: 471-476. https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262010000300019" title="Seasonality of Insects in the semi-arid Caatinga of Northwestern Brazil - Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 54: 471 - 476." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262010000300019" year="2010">Vasconcellos et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9EBCAD454B466E8085218C6FA906643E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-68.4.762" author="Beserra Nobre, CE" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterist Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="762 - 764" refId="B4" refString="Beserra Nobre, CE, Bezerra Souza, T, Vieira Nunes, R, Avello Nicola, P, Machado Pereira, LC, 2014. A new distribution record of the threatened Megasoma gyas rumbucheri Fisher, 1968 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Dynastinae) Northward to the Rio Sao Francisco, Pernambuco, Brazil. The Coleopterist Bulletin 68: 762 - 764, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-68.4.762" title="A new distribution record of the threatened Megasoma gyas rumbucheri Fisher, 1968 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Dynastinae) Northward to the Rio Sao Francisco, Pernambuco, Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-68.4.762" volume="68" year="2014">Beserra Nobre et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<normalizedToken id="71C9B204FCF998B154C8D81B9AA8A513" originalValue="“Meio-norte”">&quot;Meio-norte&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="023D0CBD510B2138639E665AADEB9F3E" originalValue="“Sertao”">&quot;Sertao&quot;</normalizedToken>
regions (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6757B9C1DAE6975357D34F8761C44DEC" captionStart="Figures 9, 10" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 9, 10. 9 Surface of bioma Caatinga in Brazil 10 The subregions in NE Brazil." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.999.53130.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481434" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">10</figureCitation>
). The Caatinga biome (xeric shrubland and thorn forest) occupies an area of 497,000 sq. miles, i.e., 10% of Brazilian territory (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F00AC6B74E3A6E33A6E7D98A3AA6A0CA" captionStart="Figures 9, 10" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 9, 10. 9 Surface of bioma Caatinga in Brazil 10 The subregions in NE Brazil." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.999.53130.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481434" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">9</figureCitation>
); it is a recent biome located on an ancient seabed. This biome experiences long periods of drought, which can last up to eight months. It is mainly composed of dry Savannah (
<bibRefCitation id="0299C7EDD205E8766D2DD009568F8A37" author="Coutinho, LM" journalOrPublisher="Oficina de Textos, Sao Paulo" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B11" refString="Coutinho, LM, 2016. Biomas Brasileiros. Oficina de Textos, Sao Paulo" title="Biomas Brasileiros." year="2016">Coutinho 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="F8610FEEC6FDF61E1C6117EF8B0F1A59" doi="10.3897/zookeys.999.53130.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481434" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" start="Figures 9, 10" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="B5F4EC77DBE4EE3067F5038167355199" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="1D5932A31FFBBB7BE2925C192DD097DA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Figures 9, 10.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="50B663472C89778B17F51132D01C9983" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">9</emphasis>
Surface of bioma Caatinga in Brazil 
<emphasis id="AA0D84E7D5ABA305C71228D2AA8E530A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">10</emphasis>
The subregions in NE Brazil.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
